## Scenario 5 — Healthcare Decon: Biological + Chemical During Maintenance
##
## Multi-hazard + confined space + maintenance. Worker enters autoclave
## room (PRCS) with residual biological contamination + glutaraldehyde
## vapor. Three OSHA standards fire simultaneously: BBP, HCS, PRCS.
## LOTO fires because it's maintenance. Bio/chem waste is RCRA mixed
## waste. NIOSH REL more protective than OSHA PEL for glutaraldehyde.
##
## Baseline triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1270).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_BioChemMaintenance rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:BiologicalHazard ,
                                  ehs:ChemicalHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:MaintenanceAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:ConfinedSpace ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:OSHA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:EPA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:NIOSH_Framework ,
                                  ehs:GHS_Framework ,
                                  ehs:ACGIH_Framework .
}
